originalText.text:
Super cool experience to be able to go see a taping of the tonight show starring Jimmy Fallon!

We have seen it twice already. First time we booked tickets online in advance, second time we stood in the stand by line. We got to the nbc store at 5:50am. We were stand by tickets number 3/4&5. We were told that stand by tickets 1 through 10 usually get in. When we came back at three we got shuffled into lines according to our stand by ticket order. By 4pm they announced which tickets got in and sure enough 1-8 were accepted right away!

The experience was super fun! Extremely well organized! If you go to stand by be there 5:30am to be sure to get in. You can‚Äôt sit while waiting so wear comfy shoes. There is a Starbucks right downstairs and a bathroom at the other end of the building. At ten they let you in the store and hand out the tickets. Then you can go back to the hotel to nap ;) or just enjoy the town until 3pm when you need to be back. Your ticket number matters at 3pm, so don‚Äôt be discouraged if a long line has formed already. They take you in order of the ticket number. Don‚Äôt bring big bags or big school bags. You have to be on time.
The peacock lounge upstairs for waiting is super nice and has a water fountain and bathroom. Once you get into the show you cannot leave until it‚Äôs done taping. It takes about 1.5hrs so you are out about 6:30! Taping starts at 5pm!

originalText.text: So much fun! We went in to see the shop, and someone working on set came up to us and asked if we wanted to sit for the rehearsal. Super cool hearing the jokes for the day before they made it on the show. Even the ones that didn‚Äôt make it on were pretty funny. Hopefully will come back around if I‚Äôm ever in New York again, and try to get tickets for the full show.
